The Transportation Cabinet shall consist of the following major organizational units:
The Office of the Secretary, which shall include, but not be limited to:
The secretary to be appointed by the Governor under KRS 12.255; and
The deputy secretary appointed under KRS 12.040;
The Department of Highways, headed by a commissioner, appointed by the Governor under KRS 12.040;
The Department of Vehicle Regulation, headed by a commissioner, appointed by the Governor under KRS 12.040. The Motor Vehicle Commission established in KRS 190.058 shall be attached to the Department of Vehicle Regulation for administrative purposes;
The Department of Rural and Municipal Aid, headed by a commissioner appointed by the Governor under KRS 12.040;
The Department of Aviation, headed by a commissioner appointed by the Governor under KRS 12.040. The Kentucky Airport Zoning Commission established by KRS 183.861 shall be attached to the Department of Aviation for administrative purposes;
The Office of Support Services, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040;
The Office of Transportation Delivery, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040;
The Office of Audits, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040;
The Office of Human Resource Management, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040;
The Office of Information Technology, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040;
The Office of Legal Services, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040;
The following offices, which shall be attached to the Office of the Secretary:
The Office of Public Affairs, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040;
The Office of Budget and Fiscal Management, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040;
The Office for Civil Rights and Small Business Development, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040; and
The Office of Inspector General, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040;
The following offices, which shall be attached to the Department of Highways:
The Office of Project Development, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040, who shall be a registered professional engineer under KRS Chapter 322, and who shall be known as the deputy state highway engineer for project development;
The Office of Project Delivery and Preservation, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040, who shall be a registered professional engineer under KRS Chapter 322, and who shall be known as the deputy state highway engineer for project delivery and preservation;
The Office of Highway Safety, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040; and
Highway District Offices One through Twelve, each district office to be headed by an executive director, also known as the chief district engineer, appointed under KRS 12.040, who shall be a registered professional engineer under KRS Chapter 322; and
The following offices, which shall be attached to the Department of Rural and Municipal Aid:
Office of Local Programs, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040; and
Office of Rural and Secondary Roads, headed by an executive director appointed under KRS 12.040.
